        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2019-02-14 03:10:00.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-11964 ldlm: Don't match kms_ignore DOM locks",
        "message": "LU-11964 ldlm: Don't match kms_ignore DOM locks\n\nDOM uses the kms_ignore flag to indicate the DOM bit is\nbeing cancelled, so if a lock with this bit set matches a\nDOM lock request, LDLM rejects it and creates a new lock.\n\nThe problem is that a lock with kms_ignore set can remain\nthe first lock in the queue, so all new requests match it\nand then reject it.  This creates a lock for every request.\n\nThe solution is to not match this lock in lock_matches,\nthen we will continue and find other locks which allow our\nrequest, rather than creating a new lock.\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ic791d20171488ab71cfb33f2537f7099212baf5f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
